{{Quote|The plague, an airborne virus, is extremely contagious to Humans, and death is speedy, certain, and painful. The last known strains are thought to have died out 46 years ago when the total loss of the Candorian colonies.|[[TriNebulon News/Legends|TriNebulon News]], about the [[Candorian plague/Legends|Candorian plague]]|<ref name="GNN5">{{JournalCite|5|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>}}
The '''Candorian colonies''' were colonies of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Candoria]].<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> In [[46 BBY]],<ref name="GNN5" /> Candoria and its colonies were depopulated by an outbreak of the [[Blue Shadow Virus/Legends|Blue Shadow Virus]].<ref name="TEA" /> The disease was later known as the [[Candorian plague/Legends|Candorian plague]]. The plague seemed to end then, but was [[Dentaal Uprising|introduced]] to [[Dentaal]] by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] forty-six [[Standard year/Legends|years]] later.<ref name="GNN5" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Candorian colonies were first mentioned in the [[1995]] magazine [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 5|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 5]] as the "'''B'''andorian colonies". As they are related to the Candorian plague, "Bandorian" was considered a misspelling of "Candorian". The correct spelling was then confirmed by the [[2009]] reference book ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''.

